reviews.text: Honestly was really good as you can see. Chicken was perfectly cooked as you cannot see because I ate all of it. The pita as well was so fluffy and soft I never thought pita could be that amazing and moist. They loaded me up with veggies too, broccolini was perfectly tender
Great pizza! Got the margarita and pepperoni. Super cute atmosphere when we went for pick up. Next time I want to dine in and try other foods.

5 stars. Good food. Clean calm atmosphere. Outstanding staff, Nick keeps the place running smooth. Well worth any wait time and any minor hiccups. Give this place a solid try and you will be pleased. FYI pizza slices rock!! Order b4 3pm though

This is a new favorite of mine. I loved the atmosphere. My daughter loved seeing kids books available to read. I order the souvlaki platter and it was delicious. Large portion. The fries were crispy and yummy. The Taziki sauce was incredible and fresh. Chicken was AMAZING and very flavorful. Everything was a 10. A table near me had slices of pizza and they were HUGE and I could hear the table talking about how yummy they were. I will definitely be back. My server was very kind and attentive. I am looking forward to going again. Lunch pricing is great especially for the portion size.

Ordered from Doordash. Everything was bland, and the fries and mozzarella sticks were stale. The portions were relatively small for the price. The baklava cheesecake was pretty good, but again quite small. Definitely overrated.

detailedReviews.author: Christopher Shindle
detailedReviews.text: Have gotten Pizza for the last 2 Saturdays (both togo).  Last night I was picking up and the togo girl was super friendly, even while dealing with challenging customers that were upset with their wait time.  Granted it was Saturday Night and the business was busy...tells me they are doing something right!  I'm patient and the pizza was worth my short wait...and the girl working the togo counter was extremely polite, poised, & professional even while dealing with adversity.  Shame on folks without patience & understanding...the food was great both times!

detailedReviews.text: One of the Best pizzas I have had, Great flavor.

detailedReviews.text: Phenomenal pizza and the GLUTEN FREE option is amazing and celiac safe! (At least for us )

detailedReviews.text: They were quite busy, as it was a Friday evening, but the food came out surprisingly fast and was absolutely delicious.

detailedReviews.author: Casey Cheff
detailedReviews.text: Our server Avaliese was amazing! She was very friendly, welcoming, and provided great service. The food was great! I would honestly say this is easily the best pizza in the area. We will definitely be coming back.

detailedReviews.text: Scuola Pizza is a great place to eat out, their Margherita Pizza was spot on, highly recommend.

detailedReviews.text: I have only gotten takeout pizza every time I order but the pizza is so delicious! My family loves it! The people that work there are all so cheerful and personable. This is my favorite place to order pizza!

detailedReviews.author: Brian Ebel
detailedReviews.text: we regularly visit Scuola's each month.  our last visit on 7/10/25, our server Bridget was AMAZING.  She was very polite, professional, and attentive.  Hopefully, we can have her again.

detailedReviews.author: Melinda Menzel
detailedReviews.text: We ate at Scuola for the first time a couple of months ago and it is my new favorite place!   I have tried quite a few things on their menu and have loved them all.  Their Chicken Marsala, Chicken Souvlaki and their pizza are my favorites, but I also really like their flaming cheese appetizer and onion rings.  We have always had great service as well.

detailedReviews.author: Sharron Peters
detailedReviews.text: Food and service was great, but the floor was bulging up a couple inches which I nearly tripped on, other wise was good time.

detailedReviews.author: Cindy Ballard
detailedReviews.text: We did carry out but its really a cute little place. We split a chicken parm and Greek salad. Plenty of food and very good. There is a spice in the sauce I cant place but it made it very unique. The Greek salad had huge chunks of feta and lots of black olives.  I recommend eating here.

detailedReviews.author: Scott K
detailedReviews.text: First of we found this hidden gem two months ago and it's amazing.  Dine in for best food ever.  They are so friendly and care about the customers.  I left my keys there and didn't realize it because my wife had the keyless fob in her purse so my vehicle still unlocked and started for entire weekend doing errands. The following week I looked everywhere.  Backtracking I finally called Scuola and they held them for the entire time.  Very cool.  That gave us an excuse to dine there again.  Try the appetizer they light on fire if your a cheese lover but be prepared to share it's a ton. Every dish is amazing.  From salad to entrees you can't go wrong.

detailedReviews.author: Phillip Bernavil
detailedReviews.text:
I made the mistake but Scoula went out of their way to make it right. After an eleven hour workday, I walked in tired and worn down. Nick did not just fix the order. He turned the whole night around.

The Chow Bella was amazing, full of flavor and comfort, but the service stood out even more. Thoughtful, quick, and genuinely kind. It is rare to feel that taken care of in a small moment, and they delivered it without hesitation.

Scoula, thank you. You made my night. I will absolutely be back.

detailedReviews.author: Laken Riess
detailedReviews.text: Great food. Great atmosphere. My husband got the chicken parmesan and I got the cheese ravioli. The servings were big enough that we both took some of ours home. I highly recommend giving this place a shot if you haven't been there yet. Bill (the owner) is very kind and welcoming to everyone!

detailedReviews.author: Zach
detailedReviews.text: Been a regular here for quite awhile. Great service, serving size is large, and the lunch deals are the best in town. Shout out to Avaliese.

detailedReviews.author: Carlos Noguerol
detailedReviews.text: Great service and food!!

detailedReviews.author: Amrutha agarwal
detailedReviews.text: I came in to eat the other week and it was phenomenal. From the food to the service, I could not have asked for a better experience. If you have not gotten the chance to have Jordan as your server you are missing out. She was so sweet, funny and you could tell that she knew the menu very well. I will 100% be going back (and especially asking for her).

detailedReviews.author: Charles Fisher
detailedReviews.text:
My wife and I stopped in for lunch. They have one door for takeout and another for the sit-down part. The decor was nice and clean. The pictures on the walls confused us because they were about reading and math.  They also had books to read for the kids.  Once we realized Scuola means School in Italian that made sense.  Also we were expecting typical Italian options.  This is more of a Mediterranean menu with many Greek choices to compliment the Italian choices.

We started with a side of meatballs (SHHH! not on the menu).  They were very good and would order again.  We then got a large Lil Sicily. Italian Sausage, Pepperoni, Ricotta Cheese, Oregano and Basil. Loved the crust. A large was too large for two so next time we will get a regular.  But looking forward to leftovers.

While the name says school its a definite date night location for us in the near future.  We look forward to tasting some Greek when we we do.

detailedReviews.author: Sue Lake
detailedReviews.text: First time hubby and I have eaten here. Highly recommended by friends. Great selection. Server was awesome. Very attentive and knowledgeable. Friendly. Excellent service. Food was delicious. We will definitely be back.

detailedReviews.author: Joanne Edde
detailedReviews.text: Found a quiet little place to have lunch between events today. Jordan personally made me a Caesar salad with grilled chicken and she and the salad were outstanding! Thank you Jordan!

detailedReviews.text: I won‚Äôt lie, when Scuola pizza first opened, I was a little apprehensive based on the number of items that were difficult to do well on their menu. I have since tried Scuola many times and consistently been impressed. I‚Äôm not how they get all of these dishes so delightfully wonderful, but they do it. I typically do takeout and get Greek or Italian (Pizza).

detailedReviews.text: I ordered 2 pizzas online for pickup at 5pm. I showed up 10 minutes early to find the pizzas on their shelf already at room temperature. I think they made the pizzas hours early. Their only solution was to reheat them. This makes me believe there are many health code violations happening here.

detailedReviews.author: matthew fabiano
detailedReviews.text: Passed this place this morning and it looked nice. Placed an order on my way home for 2 of their specialty pizzas which came out to $47 with the tax. The inside of this restaurant looks very nice, the staff is friendly and they were all smiling, but the pizza is not good, especially with that price point. Maybe try their entrees and see how it goes, but again i wouldn't order pizza here.

detailedReviews.author: M.A. Pino
detailedReviews.text: Gluten free vegan supreme was amazing! Loves this place! Eat local!

detailedReviews.author: Thad
detailedReviews.text: So decided to give them another try ... Ordered pick up which has a $3.50 which is only screwing their employees out of an extra tip. Ordered wings and a past a dish. Drove all the way over there to find out they were out of wings. (Who runs out of wings on a Sat night?) So i ended up paying $25 for a sub par pasta dish with old dried out chicken, no sundried tomatoes and dry pasta which ended up making my wife so sick she is still in bed throwing up. This place is def lacking in supervision. That dish should have never left the restaurant.

detailedReviews.author: Amanda Bray
detailedReviews.text: My husband ordered a burger with no cheese. It came with cheese. I ordered the spaghetti and the sauce is off. Tasted like chef-boyardee. Our order got delivered at 9:15 so too late to get it corrected. Ended up in the trash and had to go out and get something else to eat. My kids liked their meal but it would have been nice for the whole family to enjoy.

detailedReviews.text: More than Pizza. Pizza is some of the best in GNV, plus tons of other options. Super friendly staff. Great service.

detailedReviews.author: ravin mehta
detailedReviews.text:
Third class service.  Server don't even pay attention.  All for vegetarian and vegan, and she will get chicken where we had mentioned clearly about veg specification.
Out of bread and marinara every time they warm up. Wait for 10-15 mins again.
Plates have to be asked for. Otherwise, no plates were provided to eat.
Really bad experience. Never experienced this kind of worthless service.
Looks like they don't  know the difference between vegetarian and vegan.

detailedReviews.author: Anna Lyra
detailedReviews.text: This is my favorite vegan pizza in Gainesville! The "Vegan Supreme" comes loaded with many toppings at a great price, exuding a healthy veggie-to-bread ratio. The veggies aren't over-cooked, retaining more life force and yummy flavor. The vegan cheese is perfectly proportioned & deliciously melty! I also appreciate that they have a gluten-free option. Whether taking out or dining in, the experience is always wonderful with Scuola :D

detailedReviews.author: Stephen Muick
detailedReviews.text: Great food and service.

detailedReviews.author: Kelle Moore
detailedReviews.text: We have come here to eat several times and have been impressed every time. The food is served hot, and fresh.  Great flavor!  The wait staff is top notch and very respectful. The whole place is extra clean. Love it!

detailedReviews.author: DLS
detailedReviews.text: I love their food their pizza is great and the lamb tastes so good nice fresh and tender.

I am looking forward to going again. Lunch pricing is great especially for the portion size.

detailedReviews.text: Pizza was good other than what tasted like , looked like, and had the texture of canned mushrooms üôÅ

detailedReviews.text: Tried this place for the first time, and I was thoroughly impressed. Authentic Greek cuisine, great atmosphere, friendly and quick service. Worth every penny

detailedReviews.author: Louis Carullo
detailedReviews.text:
So our sons wanted to pick something to eat after a day out for buying gifts for each other. They wanted pizza with lasagna. We picked this place and I figured it would be good‚Ä¶

From the moment we came in to the moment we boxed up our leftovers, this place was absolutely amazing. Gyro meat could not have been more tender. The spanakopita app was absolutely fantastic and fresh. The salad fresh. The cream spinach was amazing.

I‚Äôm writing a review including the bloody cream spinach‚Ä¶my wife got the chicken marsala‚Ä¶heaven. My kids devoured the lasagna.

The server was knowledgeable, kind, the staff accommodating because our kids wanted to sit separate since it was their day.

If you aren‚Äôt in the area, make it a point to come here. You will not at all be disappointed.

detailedReviews.author: Andrea McCann
detailedReviews.text: Loved my server, she was sweet and accommodating.

detailedReviews.text: First time there, and I will go back.
